  "text": "In elemental diet induced gut atrophy (Barber et al. 1990; [CITATION_1] [CITATION_2] , supplemental glutamine (a) improved intestinal morphology; (b) increased mucosal protein content; and (c) had no effect on bacterial translocation. However, rats given Vivonex TEN, which has a high content of free glutamine, had decreased bacterial translocation compared with two other elemental diets (Alverdy et al. 1990) .",
